dcterms:creator: E. Leurent
dcterms:description: Highway-env is a Python library comprising a collection of environments for automated driving, encompassing several typical road scenarios: highway, merge, roundabout, intersection, parking, and racetrack. This study trained and tested the DRL models on the roundabout scenario, while scenarios such as highway merging were used to test and verify the model's versatility.
dcterms:title: Highway-env
